ce:section.ce:para:
Since nano-sized sorbents have a greater surface area than ordinary sorbents, lower amounts of these sorbents can result in satisfactory results. Nanocomposite in the solution was varied from 1 to 7 mg to determine the optimum amount needed for AR extraction. As the adsorbent amount increased, extraction efficiency increased, and maximum extraction efficiency was reached at 5 mg (Fig. 5

                           d
                        ). As more adsorbent is added, the %ER does not change. For all subsequent experiments, 5 mg was determined to be the optimum value [20].
